article.headline: High Point 77, Liberty 71
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 21 points to lead High Point to a 77-71 win over Liberty on Wednesday night. Jerald Minnis, Landon Quick and Mike Jefferson added 13 apiece for the Panthers (13-5). Gene Harris finished with 12 points and went 2-for-3 from the 3-point line, while Reid pulled down a team-high seven rebounds. High Point led 37-34 at halftime. Larry Blair scored a game-high 24 points for the Flames (7-11), while Alex McLean had his seventh double-double of the season with 14 points and 15 rebounds. Anthony Smith added 12 points.
